Warlord of Ayonae Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/upalarran.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Palarran</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/20/02 8:41:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1514.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Army and Flat Feet??</span><hr size=1> Out of curiosity, would having flat feet prevent me from being drafted, if the draft were reinstated and all?  Would I be taken anyway as if my feet were normal, or assigned a non-combat role, or ignored completely? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/unekosuda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>nekosuda</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New to the block</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/20/02 8:49:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1514.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Army and Flat Feet??</span><hr size=1> Part of the med screening process is looking at your feet and doing the &quot;duckwalk&quot; (those who have served know) and the flatfoot is a relative term I suppose as there are varieing degrees of flat-footedness ( I assume that fallen arches are labled as flatfooted for this argument..if I am wrong please correct me). It will depend on how severe your case is. If you have a somewhat fallen arch then you will still be considered acceptable (same goes for high arches also). If you really want in then just do not admit to wearing supports of anykind as they are a disqualifier. Remember, never volunteer any information to the medical people at the med screening place, thier job is to DQ people so the less you say the better off you are.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/umukaz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mukaz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Regular Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/20/02 4:58:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1514.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Army and Flat Feet??</span><hr size=1> Flat feet won't prevent you from being drafted. You'll have to show up for a physical exam like every other draftee. If, during the course of the exam, a condition is identified that will prevent you from entering military service <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>then</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> you are let off the hook. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=114916"><font color=blue>Ragash and his sidekick Iggy</font></a><BR>
Beastlord of Grobb <BR>Ayonae Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/unamieamuroms.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NamieAmuro MS</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Regular Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/20/02 6:06:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1514.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> Duckwalk = <br>
<br>
30 men in thier underwear walking around like a duck while a doctor walks around and examines them.<br>
<br>
*bad memory*<br>
<br>
--Namie Amuro <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/usamuelledbetter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Samuel Ledbetter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/20/02 9:15:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1514.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> I'm in the military and I have the flattest feet anyone has ever seen. When you're standing there in your undies (don't forget to wear undies to MEPS) twist your knees slightly outward and turn your feet inward until they're pointed directly forward again. There's your temporary arch. <br>
<br>
Thats exactly what I did and all I got to say is: STRESSFRACTURES MAN!! and lots of em. I developed over 200 of the fuckin things in my feet. Keep it to yourself until you get out of bootcamp though. Spending 8 months on medical hold is a worse alternative than dealing with the sharp annoying pain. Thats my medical advice for ya haha.<br>
<br>
Congratulations on your decision to join the service. I suggest joining either the Navy or the Air Force though. Navy= more money. Air Force= better quality of life. Army and Marines= sleeping in foxholes, sand in your crack, and little chance for advancement. I hit my 4 year point in 9 days and I've been an E5 for about 6 months. Thats not too terribly uncommon in the Navy, but damn near unheard of in the other branches. Just more advice for ya. <br>
<br>
Keep your feet dry. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uterhasxa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TerhasXA</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/20/02 10:04:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1514.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Flat Feet Suck!</span><hr size=1> &quot;Flat Feet&quot; Is actually a deformitity in your foot. Which happens due to &quot;fallen arches&quot; I am too lazy to go look up the clinical terms sorry. Those are the common terms though.<br>
<br>
It is possible to have rather flat feet and still get in. The question is why your feet are flat. Born that way? Ok. They are that way because of fracture, weak bones etc.... You wont get in.<br>
<br>
I have the exact opposite problem myself. My arches are terribly high. ( roughly 2 inches ) I served no probs but only after they took X-Rays etc, and gave me a waiver.<br>
<br>
From previous posts, it is good advice if they dont ask you about them dont say anything to them <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  If they see something wrong they will certainly flag it, that is their job. Don't feed them ideas. Dunno about your local MEPS station but here they have this older than dirt doc who has been around since the civil war, who gets his jollies off disqualifying people.<br>
<br>
I am sure anyone who has served in the US Armed Forces will agree with this. From the moment you walk into MEPS till you are outta your Advanced Training, STFU do what you are told, and try to blend in best you can.<br>
<br>
My boot instructors didnt even remember my name until about the 5th week <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  made life a lot easier .<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> &quot;Air Force= better quality of life. Army and Marines= sleeping in foxholes, sand in your crack, and little chance for advancement.&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Kinda agree and disagree with this. I was Air Force. The qualitity of life was nice. Army and Marines do have plenty of jobs that do not require you to be sleeping in Fox Holes though. Find a Job category that you like and go for it. Ask about bonus's too.<br>
<br>
I couldnt make up my mind, so I asked the recruiter for a list of jobs with bonus's. Found one I liked and came outta it with an extra 5k in my pocket <p>Latah,<BR>Terhas<BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=151667>My Gear!</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/bayonaero.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kaldolaf>Kaldolaf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Been around a while</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/20/02 10:23:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1514.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Flat Feet Suck!</span><hr size=1> i tell you this..<br>
<br>
you go in with flat shoes. you will have a rough time rougher then the other recruits..<br>
