just my advise.. and yes i served in the military in case you are wondering.. <p>Kaldolaf high priest of Casus Belli</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/umoonbound.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Moonbound</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New to the block</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/21/02 1:16:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1514.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Flat Feet Suck!</span><hr size=1> Wow. Thank you for all the wonderful information. After examining my feet for the past three days, I have decided they are not totally flat - only slightly if anything. Cant really tell. <br>
The reason I am joining the army is because I will soon have a college degree, hopefully ROTC status, and I want to fly a chopper. Best possible scenario - A black hawk. <br>
<br>
Its not easy, but it's what I want, so the army is the direction I must head in. Or atleast so I have been told/beleive. <br>
